  "prompt": "How many people graduate in India every year (with at least a bachelors degree)?",
  "response": "The number of people graduating in India with at least a bachelor's degree varies each year and can depend on various factors, including educational policies and the number of institutions. However, as of recent estimates, several million students graduate annually from undergraduate programs across India. According to the All India Survey on Higher Education (AISHE) report, which provides data on higher education in India, the number of graduates in a given year can be in the range of 7-8 million. For the most precise and updated figures, one should refer to the latest AISHE report or data from the Ministry of Education in India.",
